{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018hDyPj9TNUZhXxXGf18TjP","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/-\n     2→Copyright (c) 2026 Elman Project. All rights reserved.\n     3→Released under Apache 2.0 license.\n     4→Authors: Elman Project Contributors\n     5→-/\n     6→import Mathlib.LinearAlgebra.Matrix.NonsingularInverse\n     7→import Mathlib.Data.Matrix.Basic\n     8→import Mathlib.Analysis.Normed.Group.Basic\n     9→import Mathlib.Analysis.SpecialFunctions.Trigonometric.Basic\n    10→import Mathlib.Analysis.SpecialFunctions.ExpDeriv\n    11→import Mathlib.Topology.Basic\n    12→import ElmanProofs.Expressivity.LinearLimitations\n    13→import ElmanProofs.Expressivity.LinearCapacity\n    14→import ElmanProofs.Expressivity.MultiLayerLimitations\n    15→import ElmanProofs.Activations.Lipschitz\n    16→\n    17→/-!\n    18→# E88: Definitive Formalization\n    19→\n    20→This file provides the SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH for E88 architecture formalization,\n    21→crystallizing all key predictions and properties.\n    22→\n    23→## E88 Architecture\n    24→\n    25→E88 is a recurrent neural network with:\n    26→1. **Multi-head square states**: H heads, each with D×D state matrix S\n    27→2. **Nonlinear temporal dynamics**: S := tanh(α·S + outer(v, k))\n    28→3. **Independent head evolution**: Each head runs autonomous temporal dynamics\n    29→4. **Tanh saturation**: Creates stable attractors at ±1\n    30→\n    31→## Core Update Rule\n    32→\n    33→For each head h:\n    34→```\n    35→k_t = K_h · x_t          -- Key projection\n    36→v_t = V_h · x_t          -- Value projection\n    37→S_t^h = tanh(α_h · S_{t-1}^h + δ_h · outer(v_t, k_t))\n    38→```\n    39→\n    40→Where:\n    41→- S ∈ ℝ^{D×D}: Square state matrix for head h\n    42→- α ∈ (0, 2): Decay/recurrence factor\n    43→- δ ∈ ℝ: Input scaling\n    44→- tanh: Applied element-wise to matrix\n    45→\n    46→## Key Properties (Formalized Here)\n    47→\n    48→1. **Tanh Saturation/Latching**: Once |S_ij| → 1, derivative → 0, creating stable fixed points\n    49→2. **Binary Retention**: E88 can latch a binary fact; Mamba2's linear state decays as α^t\n    50→3. **Exact Counting**: E88's nested tanh can count exactly mod small n\n    51→4. **Running Parity**: Computable by E88, not by linear-temporal models\n    52→5. **Head Independence**: Each head evolves independently (no cross-head communication in state)\n    53→6. **Attention Persistence**: A head can enter \"alert\" state and stay there\n    54→\n    55→## Comparison to Linear Models (Mamba2)\n    56→\n    57→| Property | E88 | Mamba2 |\n    58→|----------|-----|--------|\n    59→| State update | S := tanh(αS + δkᵀ) | h := A(x)h + B(x)x |\n    60→| Temporal linearity | Nonlinear (tanh compounds) | Linear (collapses to Σ) |\n    61→| State retention | Latches at ±1 | Decays as α^t |\n    62→| Compositional depth | T per layer | 1 per layer |\n    63→| Can threshold | Yes | No (proven) |\n    64→| Can count exactly | Yes (mod small n) | No |\n    65→\n    66→## Main Results\n    67→\n    68→* `e88_head_state_evolution` - Formalization of single-head state dynamics\n    69→* `e88_tanh_saturation_creates_attractors` - Tanh saturation implies stable fixed points\n    70→* `e88_can_latch_binary` - Binary facts can be stored persistently\n    71→* `e88_exceeds_mamba2_retention` - E88 retention > Mamba2 exponential decay\n    72→* `e88_can_count_mod_n` - Exact counting modulo small n\n    73→* `e88_can_compute_parity` - Running parity is computable\n    74→* `e88_heads_independent` - Heads evolve independently\n    75→* `e88_attention_persistence` - Alert states persist across timesteps\n    76→\n    77→-/\n    78→\n    79→namespace E88\n    80→\n    81→open Real Matrix Finset BigOperators\n    82→\n    83→variable {d : ℕ} [NeZero d]  -- State dimension per head\n    84→\n    85→/-! ## Part 1: E88 Core Architecture -/\n    86→\n    87→/-- E88 single-head configuration -/\n    88→structure E88Head (inputDim headDim : ℕ) where\n    89→  /-- Decay/recurrence factor α ∈ (0, 2) -/\n    90→  α : ℝ\n    91→  /-- Input scaling δ -/\n    92→  δ : ℝ\n    93→  /-- Key projection matrix K: headDim × inputDim -/\n    94→  keyProj : Matrix (Fin headDim) (Fin inputDim) ℝ\n    95→  /-- Value projection matrix V: headDim × inputDim -/\n    96→  valueProj : Matrix (Fin headDim) (Fin inputDim) ℝ\n    97→  /-- Stability constraint on α -/\n    98→  α_bounds : 0 < α ∧ α < 2\n    99→\n   100→/-- E88 multi-head model -/\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"95379173-9fa9-4c3b-b84e-0caa1677a98b","uuid":"5e831886-4120-424a-9839-0f83416879c6","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/erikg/elman-proofs/ElmanProofs/Expressivity/E88Definition.lean","content":"/-\nCopyright (c) 2026 Elman Project. All rights reserved.\nReleased under Apache 2.0 license.\nAuthors: Elman Project Contributors\n-/\nimport Mathlib.LinearAlgebra.Matrix.NonsingularInverse\nimport Mathlib.Data.Matrix.Basic\nimport Mathlib.Analysis.Normed.Group.Basic\nimport Mathlib.Analysis.SpecialFunctions.Trigonometric.Basic\nimport Mathlib.Analysis.SpecialFunctions.ExpDeriv\nimport Mathlib.Topology.Basic\nimport ElmanProofs.Expressivity.LinearLimitations\nimport ElmanProofs.Expressivity.LinearCapacity\nimport ElmanProofs.Expressivity.MultiLayerLimitations\nimport ElmanProofs.Activations.Lipschitz\n\n/-!\n# E88: Definitive Formalization\n\nThis file provides the SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH for E88 architecture formalization,\ncrystallizing all key predictions and properties.\n\n## E88 Architecture\n\nE88 is a recurrent neural network with:\n1. **Multi-head square states**: H heads, each with D×D state matrix S\n2. **Nonlinear temporal dynamics**: S := tanh(α·S + outer(v, k))\n3. **Independent head evolution**: Each head runs autonomous temporal dynamics\n4. **Tanh saturation**: Creates stable attractors at ±1\n\n## Core Update Rule\n\nFor each head h:\n```\nk_t = K_h · x_t          -- Key projection\nv_t = V_h · x_t          -- Value projection\nS_t^h = tanh(α_h · S_{t-1}^h + δ_h · outer(v_t, k_t))\n```\n\nWhere:\n- S ∈ ℝ^{D×D}: Square state matrix for head h\n- α ∈ (0, 2): Decay/recurrence factor\n- δ ∈ ℝ: Input scaling\n- tanh: Applied element-wise to matrix\n\n## Key Properties (Formalized Here)\n\n1. **Tanh Saturation/Latching**: Once |S_ij| → 1, derivative → 0, creating stable fixed points\n2. **Binary Retention**: E88 can latch a binary fact; Mamba2's linear state decays as α^t\n3. **Exact Counting**: E88's nested tanh can count exactly mod small n\n4. **Running Parity**: Computable by E88, not by linear-temporal models\n5. **Head Independence**: Each head evolves independently (no cross-head communication in state)\n6. **Attention Persistence**: A head can enter \"alert\" state and stay there\n\n## Comparison to Linear Models (Mamba2)\n\n| Property | E88 | Mamba2 |\n|----------|-----|--------|\n| State update | S := tanh(αS + δkᵀ) | h := A(x)h + B(x)x |\n| Temporal linearity | Nonlinear (tanh compounds) | Linear (collapses to Σ) |\n| State retention | Latches at ±1 | Decays as α^t |\n| Compositional depth | T per layer | 1 per layer |\n| Can threshold | Yes | No (proven) |\n| Can count exactly | Yes (mod small n) | No |\n\n## Main Results\n\n* `e88_head_state_evolution` - Formalization of single-head state dynamics\n* `e88_tanh_saturation_creates_attractors` - Tanh saturation implies stable fixed points\n* `e88_can_latch_binary` - Binary facts can be stored persistently\n* `e88_exceeds_mamba2_retention` - E88 retention > Mamba2 exponential decay\n* `e88_can_count_mod_n` - Exact counting modulo small n\n* `e88_can_compute_parity` - Running parity is computable\n* `e88_heads_independent` - Heads evolve independently\n* `e88_attention_persistence` - Alert states persist across timesteps\n\n-/\n\nnamespace E88\n\nopen Real Matrix Finset BigOperators\n\nvariable {d : ℕ} [NeZero d]  -- State dimension per head\n\n/-! ## Part 1: E88 Core Architecture -/\n\n/-- E88 single-head configuration -/\nstructure E88Head (inputDim headDim : ℕ) where\n  /-- Decay/recurrence factor α ∈ (0, 2) -/\n  α : ℝ\n  /-- Input scaling δ -/\n  δ : ℝ\n  /-- Key projection matrix K: headDim × inputDim -/\n  keyProj : Matrix (Fin headDim) (Fin inputDim) ℝ\n  /-- Value projection matrix V: headDim × inputDim -/\n  valueProj : Matrix (Fin headDim) (Fin inputDim) ℝ\n  /-- Stability constraint on α -/\n  α_bounds : 0 < α ∧ α < 2\n\n/-- E88 multi-head model -/","numLines":100,"startLine":1,"totalLines":651}}}
